    "uid": "doi:10.2139/ssrn.5341272",
    "drop": false,
    "field": "economics",
    "role": "instrument",
    "bullets": [
      "373,020 geopolitical events across 193 countries from 1960 to 2024, used to build a bilateral alignment measure, with country GDP per capita as the growth outcome.",
      "Large language models, with the family not stated, compile the raw events into the alignment measure; the paper reports no validation of the extraction against a benchmark.",
      "A one standard deviation permanent rise in alignment raises GDP per capita by roughly 10 percent over 25 years, alongside gains in investment, productivity, and trade."
    ],
    "bullet_provenance": "ai",
    "models": [],
    "open_weights": null,
